    "body" : "<p>Since “this message is harmless”(see <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43003012/class-javalaunchhelper-is-implemented-in-two-places/43003231#43003231\">the @CrazyCoder's answer</a>), a <strong>simple</strong> and <strong>safe</strong> workaround is that you can fold this buzzing message in console by IntelliJ IDEA settings:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>【Preferences】- 【Editor】-【General】-【Console】- 【Fold console lines that contain】<br>\nOf course, you can use 【Find Action...】(<code>cmd+shift+A</code> on mac) and type <code>Fold console lines that contain</code> so as to navigate more effectively.</li>\n<li>add <code>Class JavaLaunchHelper is implemented in both</code></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1063891/30635988-b4003068-9e26-11e7-926f-aeca7fc09297.png\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n\n<p>On my computer, It turns out: (LGTM :b )</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1063891/30636211-68da8a9c-9e27-11e7-9a7e-ae5c3b6af4c2.png\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n\n<p>And you can unfold the message to check it again:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1063891/30636264-84d9e74c-9e27-11e7-8a8e-9c2b78a996ed.png\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n\n<p><strong>PS:</strong></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>As of October 2017, this issue is now resolved in jdk1.9/jdk1.8.152/jdk1.7.161<br>\n  for more info, see <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/43182301/922688\">the @muttonUp's answer</a>)</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7929646,
      "reputation" : 75,
      "user_id" : 6429920,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 83,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/21fd566dbe21361fac21315ed628ef86?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "gasabr",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6429920/gasabr"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1518865635,
    "creation_date" : 1518865635,
    "answer_id" : 48840632,
    "question_id" : 43003012,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have found the other workaround: to exclude <code>libinstrument.dylib</code> from project path. To do so, go to the <strong>Preferences</strong> -> <strong>Build, Execution and Deployment</strong> -> <strong>Compiler</strong> -> <strong>Excludes</strong> -> <strong>+</strong> and here add file by the path in error message.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5007360,
      "reputation" : 2389,
      "user_id" : 4024628,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/T0Kaw.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Allison",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4024628/allison"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1524146479,
    "last_edit_date" : 1524146479,
    "creation_date" : 1521483424,
    "answer_id" : 49369823,
    "question_id" : 43003012,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This was an issue for me years ago and I'd previously fixed it in Eclipse by excluding 1.7 from my projects, but it became an issue again for IntelliJ, which I recently installed. I fixed it by:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Uninstalling the JDK:</p>\n\n<pre><code>cd /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines\nsudo rm -rf jdk1.8.0_45.jdk\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>(I had <code>jdk1.8.0_45.jdk</code> installed; obviously you should uninstall whichever java version is listed in that folder. The offending files are located in that folder and should be deleted.)</p></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk9-downloads-3848520.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Downloading and installing JDK 9</a>. </li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Note that the next time you create a new project, or open an existing project, you will need to set the project SDK to point to the new JDK install. You also may still see this bug or have it creep back if you have JDK 1.7 installed in your JavaVirtualMachines folder (which is what I believe happened to me).</p>\n"
  } ],
